A man was on Monday July 30, 2018 charged at the Mombasa court for causing disturbance in a girl’s secondary school. The court heard that on July 25, jointly with others not before court Abdullahi Juma stormed in the compound of Sheik Abdalla Al-Farsy girl’s school shouting and hauling insults at teachers disrupting classes in the process. He was slapped with another count of invading the school premises without permission from the management. Mr Abdullahi also face another count of threatening the school management by saying that he was going to destroy and bring down the school. He however, denied both charges before senior principle magistrate, Henry Nyakweba and was released on 50,000 bond with surety of similar amount with an alternative of sh 10,000 cash bail. Hearing is set to be on August 13 t  